<br>
<br>
<br>
A young, Elven Paladin, with eyes all aflame,<br>
Stepped into the world to win her true name.<br>
Protection for all.  To save, heal, and defend.<br>
Her vow to the Mother, she would keep to the end.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A dark, little secret, she holds in her heart.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Her thirst for the battle and joy in her part.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Unworthy thoughts, she feels them to be,<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp That a preserver of life, in death, takes such glee.<br>
<br>
Lord Innoruuk’s knight, with ice in his heart,<br>
With friends true and loyal, and yet, still apart.<br>
His family and home, he left long ago,<br>
For the path of the lone wolf, with little to show.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hatred, the hallmark and core of his creed,<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He practices daily in word and in deed.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Kindness and charity are merely just tools,<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp To get what he wants from gullible fools.<br>
<br>
Near a streetlamp it happens on a cold Norrath night,<br>
He steps from a shadow, into the light.<br>
Lost in the city, for aid she does pray,<br>
She stops him and asks him to show her the way.<br>
<br>
             Paladin - High Elf, Shadow Knight - Dark,<br>
             One warm and caring, one cold and stark.<br>
             When gods are at war, each plays a part,<br>
             Two lives are changed in the beat of a heart. <br>
<br>
He stops and he looks at her, smiling so shy.<br>
A sudden, strange feeling, he wants to deny,<br>
To protect her and keep her, safe from all harm.<br>
Where did this come from? He thinks with alarm.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I will give her directions and send her away.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp My path is the dark one, my feet will not stray.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ever alone, it’s the way it must be,<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Women like her are not meant for me.<br>
<br>
She looks to his eyes and reads what is there,<br>
The love in his heart, to her is laid bare.<br>
But the darkness will smother it unless she is quick<br>
For he thinks love a lie and only a trick.<br>
<br>
             She tells him her secret, her love of the dark.<br>
             For evil has touched her and left there a mark.<br>
             She thrills in the battle, the blood she finds sweet,<br>
             She laughs at her foe, lying dead at her feet.<br>
<br>
In shock, he listens, could she be the one?<br>
To fight at his side till the battle is won?<br>
He feels like a deer, by the hounds brought to bay,<br>
She stands there now, waiting to hear what he’ll say.<br>
<br>
             Slowly, he kneels in the dust of the street,<br>
             As a man who has lost and concedes his defeat.<br>
             She shakes her head slowly and tells him he’s wrong,<br>
             Each completing the other, together they’re strong.<br>
<br>
So the heart of flame, the ice did melt,<br>
And Innoruuk fumes at the blow he was dealt.<br>
Tunare smiles down, a child regained,<br>
And blesses their union with joy unconstrained<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
